\pard\f0\fs28 Perennials. Leaves flat or convolute; sheaths entire. Inflorescence a lax, secund panicle. Spikelets laterally compressed, with 3-5 hermaphrodite florets. Glumes somewhat unequal, membranous, the lower 3-, the upper 5-veined. Fertile lemma rounded on the back, coriaceous in fruit, 2-fid at apex and awned from just below the sinus; veins 7-9; callus with long hairs. Palea membranous, 2-keeled, shorter than the lemma. Lodicules 2, connate laterally.
