\pard\f0\fs28 Glabrous perennials. Leaves flat; sheaths often entire; ligule membranous. Inflorescence a panicle, with trigonous main axis. Spikelets ovate to linear in outline, with 3-many florets. Glumes unequal, hyaline, 1-veined, shorter than the lowest lemma. Lemma unawned, ovate to oblong-lanceolate, rounded on the back, 5- to 11-veined. Palea about as long as lemma. Lodicules 2, more or less connate, fleshy, glabrous.
